Package: docket
Title: Automated Document Template Processing in R
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Jonathan", family = "Conrad", email = "JonathanGConrad@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Populate data from an R environment into .doc/.docx templates. Create a template document in a program such as Word, and insert a string encased in the « »  characters to flag the location (E.G: «FirstName», «LastName», «Address»). Use the getDictionary() to create a data frame containing flags and their corresponding values, then use docket() to replace the flags and create a new file containing data from the R environment.
